==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nystatin
<hw>nystatin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>NY stat</ets>e +
<ets>-in</ets>, due to its discovery in New York State.]</ety> <def>An
antifungal antibiotic, extracted from fermentation broths of the soil
actinomycete <prodby><spn>Streptomyces noursei</spn></prodby> and other
actinomycetes; called also <altname>fungicidin</altname>. It is a
polyene macrolide antibiotic, and consists of several related
components. Component nystatin A<subs>1</subs> has formula
<chform>C47H75NO17</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nyula</ent>⟦br⟧
